$\begin{aligned}
& \frac{\Delta Q}{\Delta t}=K_A A \frac{d T}{d x} \\
& \frac{d T}{d x} \text { in conductor } A=\text { slope of graph }=\sqrt{3}
\end{aligned}$
Since both conductors are connected in series, same heat current will flow in $A$ and $B$.
$\mathrm{K}_{\mathrm{B}}=\frac{\Delta \mathrm{Q}}{\Delta \mathrm{t}} \times \frac{1}{\mathrm{~A} \frac{\mathrm{dT}}{\mathrm{dn}}}=\frac{\Delta \theta}{\Delta \mathrm{t}} \times \frac{1}{\mathrm{~A} \tan 45^{\circ}}=200 \sqrt{3} \mathrm{~J} / \mathrm{m}-\mathrm{sec}^{\circ} \mathrm{C}$
